                <head>No. 523<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In response to a request for advice from the Export-Import Bank concerning a
                    proposed $200 million credit to France, the National Advisory Council approved
                    consideration of this credit at its 194th meeting on June 9. On the
                    recommendation of the Staff Committee, contained in <gloss target="#t_NAC1"
                        >NAC</gloss> document No. 1325, the action was approved without discussion.
                    The minutes of this 194th meeting and the Staff Committee document are in <gloss
                        target="#t_NAC1">NAC</gloss> files, lot 60 D 137.</p>
                <p>On June 25 the Export-Import Bank announced its decision to extend a $200 million
                    credit to the Republic of France in order that France could receive immediately
                    dollar proceeds of contracts being placed in France under the provisions of the
                    Mutual Security Program. For the text of this announcement, see Department of
                    State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin,</hi> July 21, 1952, page 105.</p>
            </div>
